    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-03-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-03-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="76"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d76">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Dawson</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Petropolis</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-03-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 18, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 130.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the subject of my No. 121 of
                    February, 15, 1904, the boundary treaty between Brazil and Bolivia, I have to
                    say that the formal ratifications thereof were exchanged here on the 10th
                    instant.</p>
                <pb facs="0196" n="108" xml:id="pg_108"/>
                <p>The bill spoken of in that dispatch for the organization of the ceded Acre
                    territory into a national territory became a law.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thomas C. Dawson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
